4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO CHIROPRACTIC
5 PRACTITIONERS; ESTABLISHING A CHIROPRACTIC LICENSE ENDORSEMENT FOR PRESCRIPTIVE
6 AUTHORITY; PROVIDING A PRESCRIPTIVE LICENSE FEE; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AND
7 AMENDING SECTIONS 37-12-101, 37-12-104, AND 37-12-201, MCA.”
8
9 WHEREAS, doctors of chiropractic are an important, integral part of health care in Montana; and
10 WHEREAS, chiropractic health care has continued to evolve as education and technology have
11 increased to meet the demands of patient care; and
12 WHEREAS, there is a shortage of physicians throughout Montana, and physicians cannot currently
13 meet the demand in many areas of the state; and
14 WHEREAS, multiple health care scopes of practice continue to be expanded to meet the growing
15 demand in patient care; and
16 WHEREAS, it is important to improve consistency and continuity of patient care for all patients; and
17 WHEREAS, there is widespread support from many health care providers in Montana to allow for
18 doctors of chiropractic to have prescriptive authority; and
19 WHEREAS, doctors of chiropractic must send patients to other providers for nonscheduled anti-
20 inflammatory or muscle-relaxant drugs, when clinically indicated, before the patients are able to be seen by the
21 chiropractor, adding unnecessary time and cost to the health care system and to patients; and
22 WHEREAS, if doctors of chiropractic had the ability to prescribe nonscheduled anti-inflammatory or
23 muscle-relaxant drugs, a patient's health, well-being, and activities of living could be restored more quickly; and
24 WHEREAS, this act offers doctors of chiropractic the choice of whether to apply for an endorsement to
25 prescribe listed, nonscheduled drugs, but the act does not require a provider to apply for an endorsement; and
26 WHEREAS, the drugs authorized in this act are not considered controlled or scheduled drugs by the
27 United States Food and Drug Administration and are not addictive or otherwise harmful when used as directed;
28 and
