8 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Prescriptive authority license endorsement -- formulary --
9 requirements -- rulemaking. (1) A chiropractor may apply to the board for a license endorsement for
10 prescriptive authority. The board may assess a fee for a prescriptive authority license endorsement application.
11 (2) A chiropractor who successfully obtains a license endorsement for prescriptive authority may
12 prescribe, obtain, and administer only the following noncontrolled, nonscheduled formulary drugs for diagnostic
13 and therapeutic use for musculoskeletal treatment and pain:
14 (a) over-the-counter analgesics;
15 (b) prescription nonsteroidal noninflammatory drugs;
16 (c) muscle relaxants;
17 (d) topical analgesics and anti-inflammatories;
18 (e) topical cortical steroids; and
19 (f) topical and oral cortical steroids.
20 (3) The board shall adopt rules establishing:
21 (a) the procedures for chiropractors to apply for a license endorsement;
22 (b) the educational qualifications required for a license endorsement, including:
23 (i) the number of hours of initial and ongoing pharmacology education; and
24 (ii) approved pharmacology continuing education programs;
25 (c) standard protocols for prescribing prescription drugs that chiropractors with a license
26 endorsement shall follow; and
27 (d) other requirements deemed reasonably necessary by the board to implement a prescriptive
28 authority license endorsement.
