8 Section 2. Section 37-12-101, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "37-12-101. Definitions -- practice of chiropractic. Unless the context requires otherwise, in this
10 chapter, the following definitions apply:
11 (1) "Board" means the board of chiropractors provided for in 2-15-1737.
12 (2) "Department" means the department of labor and industry provided for in Title 2, chapter 15,
13 part 17.
14 (3) (a) "Chiropractic" is the system of specific adjustment or manipulation of the articulations and
15 tissues of the body, particularly of the spinal column, for the correction of nerve interference and includes the
16 use of recognized diagnostic and treatment methods as taught in chiropractic colleges but does not include
17 surgery or the prescription or use of drugs means the science, art, and philosophy of things natural and the
18 science of locating and removing interference with the transmissions or expression of nerve forces in the
19 human body by the correction of misalignments or subluxations of the articulations and adjacent structures,
20 especially those of the vertebral column and pelvis, for the purpose of restoring and maintaining health or for
21 treatment of human disease primarily by adjustment and manipulation of the human structure. The term
22 includes the prescription and administration of all natural agents in all forms to assist in the healing act, such as
23 food, water, heat, light, cold, electricity, mechanical appliances, herbs, nutritional supplements, homeopathic
24 remedies, and any necessary diagnostic procedure.
25 (b) The term does not include invasive procedures, surgery, or the prescription or use of controlled
26 or dangerous drugs, except as provided in [section 1]."
